		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>So I have read this thread a few times, and thought about it for quite a long while and this is my conclusion...</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The future can only begin upon the foundations of an solid past... that said..</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>1. Fix the classes we've got. You know what I'm talking about. You can look at any class specific forum and find the fundamental aspects of that class that are broken. Freekin fix em already, sheesh. Tick Tock Clarice.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>2.&nbsp;Reasses the range of playability options in the game. We know that the envious state of "Uber" is achievable in a raid setting. This is as it should be, we exchange the diffucult task of organizing a great number of players effectively for the fast progression into personal power that we get. However, there is no mirror to this aspect. There should be content that is directed toward exchanging long periods of time and effort (quests) for equivilent levels of personal power. And no reason why this couldn't be scaled in regard to&nbsp; 3 member groups and 6. Some effort into this change came with DoN, however I have yet to see any further progress into group size + effort= power equivilency with DoDh but then I have yet to see it all so.. I couldn't say for sure.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As far as I am concerned.. those are the 2 broken legs keeping us from heading toward the horizon confident that our past can sustain our future.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>In regard to future developments... thats just the cream on the cake. But hey SoE, yur cake is kinda soggy on the bottom, so matter how much iceing ya pile on top.. ya still got a wet bum.</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Bustinface Cheetohead<br>Guild Leader / Webmaster<br><a href=http://stillmoonwitches.guildportal.com>The Witches of Stillmoon</a><br><a href=http://www.savefile.com/files/2518876>Check out the WoS music video!!</a><br><a href=mailto:moonsinger03@aol.com>Contact the Witches</a>
