<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&message.id=207352#M207352">178</a> of 205
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 883 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			The answer to the people who enjoy "old school" rules and difficulty is create a "classic play" server.  As for adding features I always felt MMO's would combine fantasy with the sims.  Here is a short list of features I would like to see added to EQ 1<br><br>* Player Housing (including ability to mount trophies from certain kills)<br>* What if players could vie for a top position of power like King or Ruler or Lord?<br>* What if players or groups could hire NPC's to help them in quests or tasks(basicly a pet)?<br>* What if players or groups or guilds control a virtual army in a RTS sub-game (like gems in EQ)?<br>* What if players could build their own house?  What if they could build taverns or shops?<br>* How about updating the old world zones with current value loot.<br>* How about updating freeport and Qeynos to be someplace worth going to.  Not to mention all the cities.<br>* What if players could tame animals for mounts (like wild drogmires in gunthak)?<br>* What if certains zones effected group or player stats.  For example a druid might receive +5 wis in a forest, but in a graveyard might get -5 wis.? Or perhaps gain certain abilites while in certain zones.<br>* What if players had more non-combat group activies like chess (in game) or other parlor games.<br>* How about training zones or NPC's to work up seldom used skills!  Perhaps you can pay a trainer to work that unused 2hs after your 65.  Or maybe quest for it.<br>* I think bringing trade skill class/exp into EQ1 would be a good idea<br>* More interactive objects in zones/dungons (like in LDON).<br>* How about a classic server for the old schoolers!<br><br>That is all I think up right now.  But any oneof those idea's would certainly liven up the game.  And especially I would like to see a player become King of a newly created city and run it sim style.  I think creating sub-games which intersect with EQ would very cool (not like Lords of EQ [shiver]).<br><br>If SOE put together in another expansion a new castle for the purpose of promoting one person or guild as ruler.  Players can then "defend it" from rival guilds or even just random groups and one guild or player will eventually control the city (sort of like EQ2 idea).  As they control it they recieve exp bonuses, loot, plat, whatever you can think of and so for those power players it's a continual challenge.  Also they could employ other players to acts as soldiers, guards or trade persons in the zone.  The city would be it's own faction.  As ruler of your virtual kingdom you can raise armies to fight say qeynos of freeport or other major cities.  You could make several "player cities" and they could only fight each other.  The possibilities are limitless.  I don't know if EQ2 let's player create furniture, but that would be a fun tradeskill.	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
