<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
digitalrexxus wrote:<BR>
<DIV>In my own gaming experience, I've left Everquest twice to play other games.&nbsp; First I left for SWG, then for EQ2, and I've come back both times.&nbsp; They simply did not have EQ's content.&nbsp; But then, what was so appealing about them?&nbsp; What elements of those games would make EQ more attractive?&nbsp; And what things would I like to see in EQ that have not been done?&nbsp; (At least, to my knowledge.)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG><FONT color=#ffff00>1.</FONT> Give us more new reasons to go to old zones.&nbsp; Put quest mobs in there, redesign them, upgrade the gear in so many of the old zones.&nbsp; They're just empty and useless as they are.</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff99>2.</FONT> <STRONG>Give us new methods of entertainment within the game.&nbsp; A real poker game, for example, or point to point races.&nbsp; Games within the game.</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>That's all I can think of for now, but I'll add more as I meditate on it.&nbsp; Thank you for your time.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV><BR>
