<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Rawlden wrote:<BR>
<DIV>I too went away (not completely) for a while to another game. WoW. Here are a few things I liked about that game (but not enough to keep me from cancelling my 2 accounts and comming back to EQ)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>No splash screen on zoning.</STRONG> - If EQ could somehow manage to eliminate the splash screen on contiguous zones, I'd love that. But still leave it so that mobs would not chase you across a zone boundary. How cool would that be to run across a zone line and be abe to turn around and stick your tongue out at the mob that can no longer reach you?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Hearthstones</STRONG> - A stone that, once an hour, allows any class to port to their bind point. - OK so SOE now has the "go home" feature. Close, but you have to log off for 6 hours to use it.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>The graphics</STRONG> - some called it "cartoony" but it was far superior to EQ2 IMHO. Combat animations are teh win!</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Quest Log</STRONG> - Ok so the Task/Mission Windows pretty much have this covered. But you are still on your own for keeping track of pre-OoW&nbsp;quests.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>In Game Tutorial</STRONG> - Each race has it's own newbie yard, but the series of quests are pretty much the same in each yard. They are well designed to teach you most of what you need to know to play your class and get you some lowbie armor items and some money by the time you are level 5 and they send you on your way to the "big city". Unfortunately, this hand holding and leading you around in a linear progression persists thruout the game. You pretty much HAVE to do the quests in order or you miss out on some skills and gear that you should really have. And everyone of a certain race pretty much has to do the same series of quests. There are very few class specific quests in WoW.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Auction House </STRONG>- Loved being able to buy/sell&nbsp;stuff while off line.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Resting Credit</STRONG> - If you camped out in an Inn or a major city, you recieved "resting credit" which doubled your xp for a time after you logged back in. The longer you camped out the longer the period of double xp lasted up to a certain max (one level I think). - EQ now lets your character heal and regen mana to full if logged out for 1 hour so I guess that's a good equivilant.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>These were some of the things I liked about WoW and would love to see things like them in EQ, but the overall community of EQ and the massive content is what brought me back. WoW just had too much the feeling of a linear video game instead of an adventure game.</DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>what is a splash screen on zoning??? when we zone mobs in eqoa, we just sow, run until mob zones back/walks back to spawn spot, with out necessarily going out of the zone, but to another quadrant of the zone, like we have highpass N/NE/NW/W/E/C/S/SW/SE zone... usually if you run in a straight line for about 25-35 seconds, you out run mob and he either zones back/walks back to his spawn spot....</P>
<P>go home feature, 6 hours to reuse??? we have return home spell in eqoa and returns you to the last spirit master you bound at... anywhere, where there is a spiritmaster, and you have faction with em, than you can talk to em, and have them bind you, to that area... our recast on return home spell is like 5 seconds i think....</P>
<P>resting credit, so if you log out for a whole hour, you regain full&nbsp;health/mana??? in eqoa we go to merchants and buy drinks, which replenish mana giving you more PoT, and food that replenishes health, by giving you more HoT.... or we have bard/power necs/enc's as mana batteries in our game...</P>
<P>the ingame tutorial sounds like, when we start off in our starting cities in eqoa but we talk to the guildmaster and he gives you first couple of quests/abilities/gear... something like lev 1/2/3/5/7/10/13/15/20 for your home's story line quests in eqoa.... like when you try to leave your town the tutorial pops up and teaches the basic mechanics of game, you have a choice to accept the tutorial or venture out on your on...</P>
<P>wow i feel like im comparing apple's to oranges, when taking a look at yall's game yall love so much, and our ps2 game we love so much....</P>
<P>o ya yall get horses and stuff, we get jipped but we have these coach masters in towns and starting cities, depending on your faction with em, they will let you sign, and they will give you a ride to another town and thats when you see a loading screen... like if i run from halas to dinbak, i never see a loading screen until i die or use a coach master, get a rez, or call of the hero... but our game has the infamous black screen of death, which is better known as bsod...</P>
<P>its going to take time to get used to the mechanics in this game, sux cuz time is not on my side... </P>	
		</td></tr>
