<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
SOE_Community wrote:<BR>
<DIV>Please see the original news post:</DIV>
<DIV>http://eqlive-new-stage.station.sony.com/news_section/newsview.jsp?story=49987</DIV>
<DIV>and feel free to reply below.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT size=2>What this means is that making future online games is a big business that is going to be increasingly competitive. I think that's good for you, and good for us. It's going to insure great games get made and I can tell you we're in this for the long haul.</DIV>
<DIV>
<P>Where are we going? What are we going to be doing to revolutionize this business? Well let me throw out just a few of the things we're thinking about here at SOE.</P>
<P>What if you could have families in MMO's? Virtual Children What if your characters could have children and pass on the family name</P>
<P>What if players could build fantastic dungeons that become part of the worlds we create with tools we give them? How would that work exactly?</P>
<P>Can MMORPGs have skill based combat?</P>
<P>What if?</P>
<P>I mention these things to be provocative.I want to make sure we're going to take what we do to the next level and that's going to mean putting some next generation ideas out there and seeing the kinds of things you actually want but I at least want to start this dialogue and stir the pot a little. We're very interested in your ideas about where things go from here.</P>
<P>John Smedley</P>
<P>President, Sony Online Entertainment </P></FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV>well if your thinking about letting us have children, it would be cool.... if you set aside a certain time frame, with the release of having virtual children, that all the good/evil children vanish to the alternate reality of norrath, or another dimension... make good/evil aligned charachters have to set differences aside, and work together to save their children... against this new terror that opposes both sides... i know i would give both my eyes(well i would try to negotiate to one eye) to save my child irl...&nbsp; you see that could be the missing link between releasing a brand new eq game and having the old eq series.... you bet your bottom dollar that any virtual parents out there would do anything they could to save their virtual children... unless their dead beat virtual&nbsp;dads/moms, that try to get away with minimum child support lol...</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>since ive been reading these boards, and seeing that over here, on this game, yall have the same problem with empty zones/starting cities... maybe yall can let us develop houses in any zone... just say i am a dwarf, and i wanna live near the dark elves... well i would have to gain faction with the neriakians, so i could build me a house in their land... you see, i want to have choices, if i want to be a good/neutral/evil dwarf... idk how it works here but i always wished in eqoa, that i could get those cute lil cudly elves to like my troll shammy in fay/teth... no matter how many orcs i killed, i was still KoS... i wanted to be the beloved troll of fay/teth lol</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>im not sure i understand what yall mean by skill based combat??? like skills in diablo II or skills when fighting, like aiming for the head/neck/arm/legs, that kind of stuff???</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>what would really be cool, if players where given tools, to develop quests and give out missions and rewards after completing the quest.... i know there are alot of creative minds out there, that could build some nice, tricky, puzzling, non-errand boy, type of kick but quests....&nbsp; im pretty sure some of those hard core gamers, would love to implement a hardcore quest, that only hardcore kinfolk could complete...&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>maybe even make specific hardcore/timesinkish uber item quests... im all about the rares, and what not, but i only complain about time sinks when they hinder player progression with xp/abilities as rewards because everyone needs their xp/abilities for player progression and development... i don't like being slowed down, because so and so is not up, or being camped heavily(i thought thats against the ToS), when its a quest i need to complete, to better my char development ingame....</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>but if there is an uber hard/timesinkish quest that gives gobs of xp to the people who completed it, hey more power to ya... you have to be able to please both types... thats why alot of hardcore diablo II people play and make new chars all the time; they like to build different char set ups with skills/uber gear... all i remember my cuz/bro inlaw telling me, is their rich because they have X amount of sojs, which is an item, that can be traded for almost any type of gear you want in game,&nbsp;depending on how many sojs you have... you see, thats what was so fun about diablo II, was building your chars up and getting uber items, then starting over, and do it all again for another char/class and learning how to play their role...</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>like the uberest item i have on eqoa, would probably be my necros two horned ripper, which was the only two handed claymore that casters could equip and stopped dropping ingame bout 2 1/2 years ago.... the item isn't really uber, its a lev 20 caster only 2h claymore sword, has like 4 lr and 6 fr or something and description says its so heavy it would cut through a tree or something to that nature....&nbsp; i have it still to this day and my necro has it equiped all the time...(ya im one of those casters/healers that actually hit the mob while casting/healing)....</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>hmmmm, im gonna try and sneak on tonite and play yalls pc version, boonbanaw is my chars name, but i have no clue what server i play on, there was only one server i could select, so maybe its that one!</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>cya l8r guys, peace out!</DIV>	
