<img src="/eq/i/icons/Classes/cleric.gif" border=0 alt=""/></a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&message.id=216163#M216163">200</a> of 205
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 176 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			The biggest thing that I see a lot of the "old timers" address is community.  Yes, it took a heck of a long time on those boat rides, took forever to get from qeynos to freeport, but that was part of the charm because it encouraged community!  <br><br>My first character was an Erudite Cleric, era 2000.  I remember being so blind at night I'd stumble around Toxx and run for dear life from the wandering heritics.  My friend made a half elf warrior and started out in Qeynos.  We soon found the boat that would take me from Erudin, past Erud's Crossing, to Qeynos.  From there we hunted the Qeynos noobie grounds, and advanced to the Qeynos hills.  I still remember my friend sayins "Oh my god!  Those bats are as big as 747s!"  <br><br>It was very rare to see anything other then erudite, human, hale elf or barbarian.  I remember seeing the first troll and ogre and was amazed.  As a matter of fact, I had my first death because an ogre warrior decided to park in the black burrow tunnel by the door, and when we had the common train, we couldn't run past him.<br><br>The point is, since you couldn't INSTANTLY go places, you had to make friends, be helpful, group, and work with others to go places.  I remember going to the Karanas for the first time.. being ganged by the bandits, lions, griffons!  I remember making my first run from qeynos to freeport... at lvl 10.<br><br>The people I saw along the way were very friendly and helpful, and went out of their way to help me succeed.  I remember waiting on the edge of kithicor, waiting for day so I could finish the run, and remember being scared to death while doing so.<br><br>I remember my first derv groups, the EC bazaar, oasis, hunting ogres after you take the raft from the oasis.  I remember the incredibly long boat trip to fayder and then on to kunark... <br><br>I made so many friends on those boat rides... and it made you feel like Norrath was extremely huge!<br><br>Sure, its so much nicer now to get the tutorial to lvl you up fast to lvl 10, have the instant ports with the pot stones (I felt that even the luclin spires were pushing it), but there is no longer any real sense of community.  <br><br>Now we have monster missions where someone can take a character from 10-70 in a week or so?  I'm not ashamed to admit that I didn't reach lvl 70 until feb or march of this year, even after playing for roughly 5 years.  Why?  Because I was focused on friends, experiencing new things, not having the pressures of a raiding guild, and helping others out.  Not to toot my own horn, but I am one of the best clerics on my server (Bertox), not because I have the best "toys", heck, my mana pool tops out at 6.8k mana!  But because I've played so long, I know when to heal, how to conserve mana, and who takes what priority on group when it comes to heals, and emergency situations.<br><br>There was an ex guildie of mine who pl'd their cleric to lvl 70 (through mm's only), and went off to join another guild.  I ask you, what use is this cleric going to be in a situation that demands the cleric know what they are doing??  None!<br><br>The fact is, becuase of the changes Sony made, the game has been dumbed down, there is literally an almost complete lack of community, Norrath and Luclin don't have the "size feel" to them anymore, and people can level so fast that I hardly trust grouping with someone 65+ anymore unless I know them.  Thankfully, I have 300AAs, a ton of defensive AA's, and the ability to use 3 DA's... (snide remark thre).  <br><br>I've done a few DoN creator missions, where we were all 70, and the mission took either 3 hours to do or we continiously wiped because the tank didn't know how to do his job (getting aggro on the right mob, right away), the puller kept pulling trains, the slower would either slow too soon (creating instant agro), ot slow too late, forcing me to burn mana keeping the tank alive.  Creator should take 15-20 mins, no longer.  But because these people don't know how to play their classes, thats what happens.<br><br>You want to make this game better?  Help the came return to the sense of community that was once there, and stop making it so easy to level.... make players actually LEARN their classes!<br><br>And yes, I absolutely agree, the bazaar needs to go.  And if a "classic" EQ server ever rears its head, I'll be one of the first players there.<br><br>Ebins Ebens<br>70 Cleric of Quellious<br>Bertoxx<br>http://digitalhonesty.org/eq/index.htm
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Ebins Ebens<br>70 Cleric<br>http://digitalhonesty.org/eq/<br><br>Rezzing Ranjas Since 2000
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
